css: cascading style sheet.
to adding styles to html pages, 
colors, background, borders, spaces, align the content, animation,

3types of css:
    1 inline css,
    2 internal css,
    3 external css


    <img style="width:300px;height:200px;">

    1. Inline css: with in the open tag, adding css propetes using style property.

    ex: <img style="width:300px;height:200px;">.

    //1inlinecss.html


    3 external css:
    by using link tag, we are adding external css file in to html page.
    <link href="style.css" rel="stylesheet">


    properties:

    size: 
        width: 200px or 20pt or 2.3rem or 20%;
        height: 200px or 20%;
        Note: we can add size only for block content including image tag.
        //1inlinecss.html
    
    background:
        background: blue or #343434 or rgb(25,0,0);
        background: url("img/1.jpg");

    border:
        border: 2px solid red;
        border-bottom:
        border-top:
        border-left:
        border-right:2px dashed red;
        border-size: 2px;
        border-style: solid;
        border-color: red;
    //2border.html    

    margin: to add spaces outside the tag(external spaces)
        margin: 20px;
        margin-left:
        margin-right:
        margin-bottom:
        margin-top:
        margin: 20px 50px 30px 10px;(top right bottom left);
        margin: 10px 30px;//(top&bottom, left&right);
        margin: 10px auto;//(top&botom left&right); 
        Note: auto to add equal spaces only on left and right if width is available.
        only for block element, we can use auto margin.
        
    // 2border.html       

    padding: to add spaces inside the tag.
        padding: 20px;
        padding: 10px 20px 30px 40px;
        padding: 10px 20px;

    //3padding.html

    float: to align the tags to left to right / right to left.
        float: left or right or none;
        by using float, we can add width and height to the inline tags.
    //4float.html

    clear: to remove float 
        clear : left or right or both;
    //5clear.html    

    text:
        color: red or #233223 or rgb(2,3,4);
        text-align: center or left or right or justify;
        line-height: 30px; // to add height of the line.
        note: to add vertically center to the text if only one line of text to the tag.
        text-decoration: none | underline | overline | line-through

    border-radius: 30px; // to add curves to the tags
    Note : width = height = borderradius then will get circle shape tag.


    ul:
    list-style: none; //to remove the bullets

    Psuedo classes:
        :hover {
            //properties when mouse over
        }    

    overflow: hidden or auto; note: hiehgt is required to add overflow property

    position:
     relative-relative to its current position.
     //position-relative.html
     absolute-relative to its parent position.
     fixed-relative to its current position and fixed.

    top: 50px;
    bottom: 50px
    left: 50px
    right: 50px
    z-index: -1 or +1

    visibility: hidden or visibile;
        hidden- to hide the tag , it will consume the spaces.
    display:none- to hide the tag, it will not consument the spaces.